Key Match Events: Boston Red Sox's Tyler O’Neill celebrated his two-run home run that also drove in Rafael Devers during the first inning of a game against the Chicago White Sox.
Trevor Story returned after missing 133 games with a shoulder injury and helped the Red Sox beat the visiting Chicago White Sox 7-5.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Alex Cora referred to Trevor Story as the 'quarterback' of the team, emphasizing his importance.
Trevor Story expressed that his return and contribution to the win meant a lot to him.
